tsc clean (exit 0). No spec files exist for these components, so there are no comment/comment-form tests to run.

## Summary

Fixed bug I4 in `C:\repos\dflow\designflow-frontend` (branch sandbox-albert). Two files changed; changes left in the working tree (no commit/push).

### File 1: `src\app\pages\comments\comments\comments.component.ts`

Injected `MatSnackBar` and added an error branch to the `addComment` POST.

Before:
```ts
import { CommentFormComponent } from '../comment-form/comment-form.component';
...
constructor(public itemService: itemService) {
}
...
this.itemService.addComment(comment).subscribe(data => {
  const commentId = data.id;
  if (form.files.length > 0) {
    this.addAttachments(commentId, form.files)
  } else {
    this.getComments()
  }
  this.activeComment = null;
})
```

After:
```ts
import { MatSnackBar } from '@angular/material/snack-bar';
import { CommentFormComponent } from '../comment-form/comment-form.component';
...
constructor(public itemService: itemService, private snackBar: MatSnackBar) {
}
...
this.itemService.addComment(comment).subscribe({
  next: (data) => {
    const commentId = data.id;
    if (form.files.length > 0) {
      this.addAttachments(commentId, form.files)
    } else {
      this.getComments()
    }
    this.activeComment = null;
    // Only clear the editor once the POST succeeded...
    this.childComponent?.clear();
  },
  error: (err) => {
    console.error(err);
    this.snackBar.open('Failed to post comment. Please try again.', 'Close', { duration: 3000 });
  }
})
```

### File 2: `src\app\pages\comments\comment-form\comment-form.component.ts`

Removed the unconditional reset from `onSubmit`; moved clearing into a new `clear()` method the parent calls on success.

Before:
```ts
onSubmit(): void {
  this.handleSubmit.emit({ text: this.form.value.title, files: this.files });
  this.form.reset();
  this.closeMention();
}
```

After:
```ts
onSubmit(): void {
  // Do not clear the editor here...
  this.handleSubmit.emit({ text: this.form.value.title, files: this.files });
}

/** Clears the editor/form. Called by the parent once a submit succeeds. */
clear(): void {
  this.form.reset();
  this.files = [];
  this.resetFileInput();
  this.closeMention();
}
```

### How text is now preserved on failure
- `onSubmit` no longer touches the form, so the typed comment (and selected files / mention state) stays in the editor after emitting.
- The parent clears the editor only inside the `next` (success) callback via `this.childComponent?.clear()`. On error, only the snackbar fires — the editor is untouched, so the user can retry.
- Reply/edit forms (rendered inside `comment.component` via `isReplying()`/`isEditing()`) are handled by the same logic: `activeComment` is set to `null` only in the success branch, so on success the reply form unmounts (clears itself), and on failure it stays open with text intact.

### Conventions followed
- Snackbar matches existing usage: `snackBar.open('...', 'Close', { duration: 3000 })`.
- `MatSnackBar` injected via Angular DI; `MatSnackBarModule` is already provided app-wide in `app.module.ts`, so no module wiring was needed.
- No `.toPromise()`, no new `window` globals. Used `subscribe({ next, error })` rather than `firstValueFrom` to keep the success path behavior byte-for-byte identical.

